Job Description
Contribute to the success of the NonStop Systems Engineering team within Issuer Processing, with emphasis on the following responsibilities:

  Provide platform support &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(hardware, operating system and middleware) for Visa’s HPE NonStop &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(Tandem) servers.
  Respond to system alerts and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;error messages to ensure continuous system availability.
  Coordinate scheduled and non-scheduled &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(emergency break/fix) hardware changes with vendor hardware engineers, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;pursuant to Visa’s rigorous change management procedures.
  Plan changes, configure, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;monitor and troubleshoot the HPE NonStop Operating System and related &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;middleware subsystems in response to changing requirements.
  Collaborate with multiple teams &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;– network, engineering, operations and applications – to ensure seamless &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;installations, deployments and system upgrades.
  Participate in off-hours and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;on-call support duties, which will periodically include overnight and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;weekend work.

Qualifications
Candidate must have:

  10+ years of systems &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;engineering experience, specific to the HPE NonStop (Tandem) platform.
  Demonstrated expertise &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;configuring Tandem subsystems, such as Spooler, Pathway, TCP/IP (including &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SSL/SSH), TMF, KMSF, EMS, Safeguard, VLE, etc.
  Strong communication skills, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(verbal and written), with emphasis on technical documentation and related &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;topics.
  Current residency in Singapore, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;or willingness and ability to relocate to Singapore upon placement. Telecommuting &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;is not an option for this position.

Preferred candidate would have:

  Demonstrated system programming &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;skills in one or more of these languages: TACL, C/C++, and/or TAL.
  Experience with CLIM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;configuration, maintenance and troubleshooting, including both TCP/IP and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Storage variants.
  Experience with configuring and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;using NonStop Open System Services (OSS), including shell scripting.
  Working knowledge of NonStop &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SQL databases (both MX and MP)
  Experience with NonStop X &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;server hardware.
  Experience with virtualized &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;storage, including XP-series storage arrays and SMF.
  Working knowledge of one or &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;more of these third-party software products:
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&gt;&gt; &nbsp;Integrated Research (IR) Prognosis.
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&gt;&gt; &nbsp;XYPRO Xygate Security Suite.
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&gt;&gt; &nbsp;Data Express
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&gt;&gt; &nbsp;Connect:Direct (NDM)

Desirable Certifications include:

  ITIL
  SSCP or CISSP
  HPE NonStop: CSE or MSE
